    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-09-03T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-09-03T16:00:00-05:00" n="339"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d339">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">845.5018/47: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Officer in Charge at New Delhi</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Merrell</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-09-03T17:00:00-04:00"
                            >September 3, 1943—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>425. Your 583, August 26, 5 p.m. The Department is informed by the India Supply
                    Mission that no wheat has yet been shipped from Canada or the United States,
                    that the ISM<note n="73" xml:id="d339fn73">India Supply Mission.</note> is
                    endeavoring to ship 5,000 tons during September, and that difficulties being
                    encountered—including both shortage of ships and shortage of bags—render even
                    this small shipment doubtful.</p>
                <p>For your confidential information, it is not thought that American ships will be
                    available to assist unless strong representations regarding the matter are made
                    by the American military authorities in India. If the latter feel that the
                    arrival of some grain from this continent would be helpful in forestalling
                    developments prejudicial to such military effort as may be contemplated from
                    India, a statement to that effect to the War Department by the CBI<note n="74"
                        xml:id="d339fn74">China–Burma–India.</note> Command Would undoubtedly be
                    very helpful. If you learn that any such representations are being made, the
                    Department would appreciate being informed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
